# Frontend Conventions (Vue 3 + Pinia)

## Component system — always use App* components
Never use raw HTML elements in views or feature components.
Use the design system from `frontend/src/components/ui/` and `frontend/src/components/layout/`.

| Raw element | Use instead |
|-------------|-------------|
| `<button>` | `<AppButton>` |
| `<input>` | `<AppInput>` |
| `<select>` | `<AppSelect>` |
| `<table>` | `<AppTable>` |
| `<div class="modal">` | `<AppModal>` |
| Loading spinner | `<AppLoader>` |
| Empty state | `<AppEmptyState>` |
| Page header | `<AppPageHeader>` (from layout/) |

Import via barrel: `import { AppButton, AppInput } from '../components/ui'`

## Stores (Pinia)
All API state lives in `frontend/src/stores/`. Views read from stores, not raw axios.
Available stores: `auth`, `feeds`, `publish`, `campaigns`, `credentials`, `notifications`, `posts`, `workspaces`, `syncOps`, `oauthApps`, `users`, `toast`, `activityLog`.

## API calls
- Axios is only allowed in stores and composables. Never import axios in a view directly.
- All `/api/*` calls are relative paths — Vite proxies them in dev.

## Composables
Reusable async/form logic → `frontend/src/composables/`.
Available: `useForm`, `useToast`, `useConfirm`, `useAsync`.

## Script style
Always use `<script setup>` — no Options API, no `export default {}`.

## Social platform display
Use `<SocialPlatformLabel type="instagram" />` for any platform label/icon — never hardcode platform strings in templates.

## Lint
```bash
npm run lint        # check
npm run lint:fix    # auto-fix
```
